R Notebook

Spinach heated to 90 or 100 degrees Celcius was vacuum packed and stored for 0, 1, or 2 weeks before the packages were opened and chill-stored in normal atmosphere for 0, 1, or 2 days. Then, the colour was measured on a Hunter Lab. Two of the colour coordinates, a and b (measuring, respectively, something like red and yellow colour), were recorded, and are given in the data set below. The variable batch is a blocking variable referring to two batches of spinach. The data is available in the file spinage.txt and listed here:

Load data

# install.packages("lmerTest")
library(lmerTest)
library(emmeans)
data <- read.csv("https://www2.compute.dtu.dk/courses/02429/Data/datafiles/spinage.txt")
data$batch <- factor(data$batch) 
data$temp <- factor(data$temp)
data$weeks <- factor(data$weeks)
data$days <- factor(data$days)
